      "writtenOn": "2026-03-02T15:51:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is some wild type abusing here. The left parameter (`a`) of the operator should be the accumulated type (you start with `std::string` here), right parameter (`b`) is the actual path (type of the vector data).\nYou take those two `path`s and create a string from them, effectively creating `string` which is then implicitly converted into a `path` again in next iteration.\n\nI recommend changing the op to something like\n\n```\n[](const std::string\u0026 acc, const std::filesystem::path\u0026 dir) {\n    return acc.empty() ? dir.string() : acc + \":\" + dir.string();\n});\n```",
